          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M,N\in \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IS.xml" title="matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link> over the same semiring with the same dimensions. We will write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\oplus  N\in \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for the <html:em><html:strong>(pointwise) addition</html:strong></html:em> of the two matrices:</html:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 {\mathopen {}\left (M\oplus  N\right )\mathclose {}}_{i,j} = M_{i,j} \oplus  N_{i,j}
]]></fr:tex>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>20</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>jms-00JP</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JP.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="the zero matrix">the zero matrix</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A <html:em><html:strong>zero <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IS.xml" title="matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrix</fr:link></html:strong></html:em> is one that whose cells all contain <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0]]></fr:tex>. In particular, we have:</html:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \begin {aligned}
   \mathbf {0} &\in  \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}\\
   \mathbf {0}_{i,j} &= 0
 \end {aligned}
]]></fr:tex>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
              <fr:contributor>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/marcelofiore.xml" title="Marcelo Fiore" addr="marcelofiore" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link>
              </fr:contributor>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>17</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>jms-00I7</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="relation">relation</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A <html:em><html:strong>(binary) relation</html:strong></html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> from a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>, written <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } B]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\in  \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\subseteq  A\times  B]]></fr:tex>. We shall typically write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {R}b]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (a,b\right )\mathclose {}}\in  R]]></fr:tex>. More generally, a <html:em><html:strong>relation between multiple sets</html:strong></html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (A_i\right )\mathclose {}}_{i\in  I}]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a subset of the cartesian product <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\prod _{i\in  I} A_i]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
              <fr:contributor>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/marcelofiore.xml" title="Marcelo Fiore" addr="marcelofiore" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link>
              </fr:contributor>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>17</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>jms-00IG</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IG.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="the empty relation">the empty <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7.xml" title="relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>For any two sets <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>, we may form the <html:em><html:strong>empty <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7.xml" title="relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></html:strong></html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varnothing \colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } B]]></fr:tex> that relates <html:em>no</html:em> elements. In other words, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varnothing ]]></fr:tex> is the empty subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\times  B]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>17</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>jms-00IZ</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IZ.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="the relation associated to a matrix">the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7.xml" title="relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link> associated to a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IS.xml" title="matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrix</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> be an <html:em><html:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (n\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-<fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7.xml" title="relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">matrix</fr:link></html:span></html:strong></html:em> over a semiring <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>. We define the <html:em><html:strong><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7.xml" title="relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link> associated to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex></html:strong></html:em> below:</html:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \begin {aligned}
 \operatorname {\underline {rel}}_S{M} &\colon  {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}\mathbin {\nrightarrow }{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}
 \\
 i\mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_S{M}\right )\mathclose {}}} j &\Longleftrightarrow  M_{i,j} = 1
 \end {aligned}
]]></fr:tex>
            <html:p>We have defined a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_S\colon  \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}\to \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}},{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
